### Admin Register Walk-in Patient Examples
### Use these examples to test the new admin patient registration endpoint

### Example 1: Register patient only (no appointment)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/admin/patients/register/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "username": "walk_in_patient_1",
  "email": "patient1@example.com"
}

###

### Example 2: Register patient with custom password
POST http://localhost:8000/api/admin/patients/register/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "username": "walk_in_patient_2",
  "email": "patient2@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

###

### Example 3: Register patient AND create appointment
POST http://localhost:8000/api/admin/patients/register/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "username": "walk_in_patient_3",
  "email": "patient3@example.com",
  "hospital_id": 1,
  "department_id": 2,
  "symptoms": "Fever and cough for 3 days",
  "notes": "Walk-in patient - paid cash at reception (Rs. 500)"
}

###

### Example 4: Register patient without email (useful for elderly patients)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/admin/patients/register/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "username": "elderly_patient_1",
  "hospital_id": 1,
  "department_id": 3,
  "symptoms": "Regular checkup",
  "notes": "Elderly patient, no email address available"
}

###

### Example 5: Just username (minimum required)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/admin/patients/register/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "username": "emergency_patient_1"
}

###
